President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on July 17, 2017, marking the first Made in America Day and recognizing the contributions of American workers and job creators to the nation's prosperity and strength. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of American work ethic, quality craftsmanship, and innovation in driving the economy and supporting military strength. President Trump is committed to promoting American manufacturing, opening markets for American producers, and protecting businesses from unfair trade practices. The proclamation also declares the week of July 16 to July 22 as Made in America Week and calls upon Americans to pay tribute to the builders, ranchers, crafters, and all those who contribute to making America great.